title: Central New York golf: Te Cleland named SWDGA Player of the Year
text:
Teresa "Te" Cleland (right) earned SWDGA Player of the Year honors while 2014 player of the year Lauren Petty came in second in the point standings. M.F. Piraino
Teresa "Te" Cleland, a member at Bellevue Country Club, was named Player of the Year by the Syracuse Women's District Golf Association for the 2015 season while Carrie Baptiste earned the Louise Suggs Award. Both awards were announced last month.
SWDGA Player of the Year is given to the golfer who accumulates the most points for low gross scores throughout the season.
Cleland, 56, won her fifth career SWDGA Championship last August. Lauren Petty (Timber Banks), the 2014 player of the year and this year's Post-Standard Women's Amateur champion , finished second in the point standings. The P-S Women's Amateur does not count toward the SWDGA player of the year award.
Baptiste (Cavalry Club) earned the Louise Suggs Player of the Year Award which is given to the SWDGA golfer who accumulates the most points for low net scores throughout the golfing season.
Katie Walsh (Bellevue CC) was named the SWDGA scholarship winner. Walsh, a 2015 graduate of Baker High School in Baldwinsville, is competing at Le Moyne College.
Here is a listing of the SWDGA tournament place-winners from the past season.

1st: Te Cleland, Bellevue
2nd: Lauren Petty, Beaver Meadows
